  "doc_id": "58792",
  "text": "We recently described a method for molecular profiling of activated neurons in the mouse brain [CITATION_1] . This approach takes advantage of the fact that ribosomal protein S6 is phosphorylated following neural activity [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] ). These phosphorylated ribosomes can then be immunoprecipitated from mouse brain homogenates, enriching for the mRNA expressed in a subpopulation of activated cells ( Figure 1A) .",
